Explanation of each part
1. Pagination
const page = Number(req.query.page) || 1;
const limit = Number(req.query.limit) || 5;
const skip = (page - 1) * limit;

If URL is:

/api/files/all?page=2&limit=5

Then:

page = 2
limit = 5
skip = 5

Meaning:

Skip first 5 files
Show next 5 files
2. Search
query.filename = {
  $regex: search,
  $options: "i"
};

If URL is:

/api/files/all?search=cat

Then MongoDB searches filenames containing "cat".

Examples matched:

cat.png
mycat.jpg
CatPhoto.jpeg

$options: "i" means case-insensitive.

3. Filter
/api/files/all?type=image

Will only show image files because regex checks filename ending:

\.(jpg|jpeg|png|gif|webp)$

Similarly:

/api/files/all?type=pdf

Will only show PDF files.

4. Sorting
/api/files/all?sort=latest
/api/files/all?sort=oldest
/api/files/all?sort=name-asc
/api/files/all?sort=name-desc

MongoDB sort values:

1   -> ascending
-1  -> descending

Example:

{ createdAt: -1 }

Means newest files first.

5. Final Database Query
const files = await File.find(query)
  .sort(sortOption)
  .skip(skip)
  .limit(limit);

This is the most important line.

It means:

Find matching files
Sort them
Skip some records
Return limited records

Example request:

GET /api/files/all?search=cat&type=image&page=1&limit=3&sort=latest

Meaning:

Search files containing "cat"
Only image files
Show page 1
Only 3 results
Latest first

