what is regex

Regex means Regular Expression.

It is a special pattern used to search or match text.

For example:

const text = "cat.png";

If you want to check whether "cat.png" contains "cat":

/cat/

This regex matches:

cat.png
mycat.jpg
CatPhoto.jpeg

In MongoDB:

query.filename = {
  $regex: search,
  $options: "i"
};

If:

search = "cat"

Then MongoDB searches filenames containing "cat".

$options: "i" means case-insensitive.

So it will match:

cat.png
Cat.png
CAT.jpeg

Another example:

$regex: "\\.pdf$"

This regex means:

\\. → actual dot .
pdf → letters pdf
$ → end of string

So it matches:

notes.pdf
report.pdf

But not:

pdfnotes.jpg
pdf-image.png

Example image regex:

\\.(jpg|jpeg|png|gif|webp)$

Meaning:

filename should end with:
jpg
jpeg
png
gif
webp

Matches:

photo.jpg
cat.png
image.webp

Does not match:

document.pdf
music.mp3

You can think of regex as:

A smart text searching rule

Some common regex symbols:

.      -> any character
*      -> repeat many times
$      -> end of string
^      -> start of string
|      -> OR
()     -> group

Example:

/^cat/

Means filename should start with "cat":

cat.png ✅
catphoto.jpg ✅
mycat.png ❌

Example:

/cat$/

Means filename should end with "cat":

mycat ✅
catphoto ❌
